tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or close to normal ranges. Mildly low creatinine and calcium are likely not clinically significant, especially if stable and without symptoms. Glucose control (HbA1c and fasting glucose) is good. No evidence of renal dysfunction or electrolyte imbalance. Recommend routine monitoring; correlate with clinical context if symptoms arise.
